In this article, the author discusses the progress made in supporting small businesses and leveling the playing field in federal contracts under the Biden administration. They highlight that the first two years of Biden's presidency saw a record number of Americans applying to start small businesses. The Small Business Administration's report shows that $163 billion went to small businesses in federal contracts, a record amount. Additionally, the administration's policies have supported one million jobs in small businesses in the last fiscal year. The report also indicates progress in increasing the share of federal contracts going to small disadvantaged businesses. The author emphasizes that Vice President Harris and President Biden are committed to ensuring that federal investments benefit underserved entrepreneurs and small business owners in all communities. They argue that investing in small business entrepreneurs is crucial for promoting competition and job creation.